Use Cases:

- I send a thousand messages in less than a tenth of a second. What will happen?

- Sanitize input.

- Login a thousand times in a second.

- Create an account with a name with code within it. (sanitize account names)

- As part of Microsoft SDL practice #6, requires a cryptography standard.

- After build, run penetration testing and static code analysis.

- Write an incident response process to handle incidents
